@startuml
title FireMapSim-v2 — UI ↔ Agent ↔ Plan Sync (current)

actor User

box "Frontend (Next.js Client Components)" #EEF
participant "CedarCaptionChat\n(UI chat + tool-output parser)" as Cedar
participant "ProjectAgentChatHost\n(@ai-sdk/react useChat)" as Host
participant "ProjectWorkspace\n(Workspace store + map UI)" as Workspace
participant "ProjectWorkspaceStore\n(useSyncExternalStore)" as Store
participant "Map Workspace\n(Leaflet + panels)" as Map
end box

box "App Server (Next.js Route Handlers)" #EFE
participant "POST /api/agent\n(Mastra handleChatStream)" as ApiAgent
participant "POST /api/simulation/run\n(DEVS-FIRE run + persist)" as ApiRun
participant "PUT /api/project/:id\n(persist plan/chat)" as ApiProject
end box

box "Agentic AI Layer (Mastra)" #FFE
participant "fireSimAgent\n(Fire Simulation Planner)" as Agent
participant "Tools\nupdate-plan / run-simulation /\nplayback-control / reset-project /\ngeocodeAddress / fetchWeather" as Tools
end box

box "External + Data" #F9F9F9
participant "Clerk Auth" as Clerk
participant "Supabase (Postgres)" as Supabase
participant "DEVS-FIRE Server" as DevsFire
participant "Weather + Geo Providers\n(Open-Meteo, Nominatim,\nOverture/Overpass)" as WxGeo
end box

== Setup / Chat loop ==

User -> Cedar : Type prompt\n(e.g. "Set location to Yosemite")
Cedar -> Host : sendMessage(text)
Host -> ApiAgent : POST messages[] +\n{ mode, planSnapshot, threadId }
ApiAgent -> Clerk : auth.protect()\n+ currentUser()
ApiAgent -> Supabase : upsertLocalUserFromClerk()
ApiAgent -> Agent : handleChatStream(\nagentId="firesim-agent"\n+ system RUNTIME_CONTEXT )
Agent -> Tools : (optional) geo-geocode-address
Tools -> WxGeo : Geocode address/place
Agent -> Tools : (optional) weather-fetch-weather
Tools -> WxGeo : Fetch current/hourly weather
Agent -> Tools : update-plan(patch)\n(no legacy fenced blocks)
Tools --> Agent : { patch: {...} }
Agent --> ApiAgent : stream UIMessage parts\n(includes tool outputs)
ApiAgent --> Host : stream response
Host --> Cedar : messages updated

note over Cedar
Parses tool outputs from assistant messages:
- tool-update-plan / dynamic-tool(update-plan) => patch
- run-simulation / playback-control / reset-project => commands
(Legacy ```setup-update``` still supported but discouraged)
end note

Cedar -> Workspace : onUpdatePlanPatch(patch)
Workspace -> Store : applyLoosePlanPatch(patch)\n+ normalizeIgnitionPlan()
Store --> Map : subscribers re-render\n(boundary/ignitions/weather panels)
Map --> User : Visual feedback\n(boundary, pins/lines, badges)

== Agent-triggered commands ==

alt Agent requests a run
  Agent -> Tools : run-simulation({simulationTimesteps?})
  Tools --> Agent : { action:"run-simulation", ... }
  Cedar -> Workspace : onAgentCommand(run-simulation)
  Workspace -> ApiRun : POST { projectId, plan, simulationHours,\nweatherOverrides }
  ApiRun -> Clerk : auth.protect()
  ApiRun -> Supabase : verify project owner\n+ upsert latest simulation
  ApiRun -> DevsFire : connectToServer()\n+ set parameters/terrain\n+ set ignitions/fuel breaks\n+ runSimulation()
  ApiRun --> Workspace : { operations, latestSimulationReplay,\nweatherUsed/weatherSource }
  Workspace --> User : "Simulation ready"\n+ replay available
else Agent controls replay
  Agent -> Tools : playback-control(play|pause)
  Cedar -> Workspace : onAgentCommand(playback-control)
  Workspace --> User : replay play/pause
else Agent requests reset
  Agent -> Tools : reset-project()
  Cedar -> Workspace : onAgentCommand(reset-project)
  Workspace --> User : opens reset confirmation modal
end

== Background persistence (debounced) ==

Workspace -> ApiProject : PUT persisted payload\n(title, plan, weather,\nworkflowMode, agentChatMessages)
ApiProject -> Clerk : auth.protect()
ApiProject -> Supabase : update map_projects\n(+ chat_messages table when present)
@enduml
